But man, after the Russian, there was all over after that in Rocky 4.

33:35.010 --> 33:49.174
Man, I loved watching Rocky because it was a guy who was failing, and failing, and failing, and then he'd have a little success, and then he'd fail, and fail, and then he'd beat Apollo, and then he would fail, and then he'd beat Mr. T, and then he would fail, and fail, and then he would beat the Russian.

33:49.374 --> 33:51.959
I mean, you can't get better movies than this for children.

33:52.099 --> 33:54.163
This is actually essential to their development.

33:54.603 --> 33:56.146
Show your children Rocky.

33:57.602 --> 34:03.910
They need to understand that failure is part of success and it's good and it's okay and they're going to fail.

34:04.251 --> 34:05.973
This is working on the mental game.

34:05.993 --> 34:06.874
Is this making sense?

34:06.914 --> 34:07.275
Yes or no?

34:09.818 --> 34:11.040
Man, I want you to have an upgrade.

34:11.701 --> 34:13.023
I want your life to go to the next level.

34:13.063 --> 34:14.705
I want my life to go to the next level.

34:15.606 --> 34:18.390
I want my marriage to get better, my relationship with God to get better.

34:18.410 --> 34:20.232
I want my parenting skills to get better.

34:20.252 --> 34:21.574
I want all of it to get better.

34:22.575 --> 34:23.697
But it starts right here.

34:23.877 --> 34:27.602
Every upgrade in your life and my life begins with an upgrade between our ears.

34:28.802 --> 34:42.701
My challenge to you is to meditate, to get something in your mind and hang over it and grow over it and take it in and mull it over it and take it in and ingest it until it becomes a new way to think.

34:43.923 --> 34:52.375
Now, a couple of years ago, actually many years ago, I had some new thoughts come into my mind that I hadn't heard before.

34:53.596 --> 34:54.738
I was a teenager.

34:55.298 --> 34:59.523
My thought process was if there is a God, he probably won't love me, because I'm just not a good kid.

35:00.364 --> 35:00.804
And I wasn't.

35:02.706 --> 35:05.810
And my mom would tell me about God, and you know, but kids don't listen to their moms.

35:05.830 --> 35:06.911
I mean, some do.

35:06.951 --> 35:08.933
I didn't.

35:10.535 --> 35:20.786
But for whatever reason, I ended up going to church, and I heard from the preacher, and the preacher said, you know what, no matter what you've done, no matter where you've been, no matter how much you've sinned, no matter how bad you think you are, there's a God who loves you.

35:22.082 --> 35:23.164
And he's willing to forgive you.

35:23.204 --> 35:28.531
In fact, he proved it by sending his son, his very own son, his one and only son to this earth to dine across for your sin.

35:28.551 --> 35:33.338
And I'm sitting there listening to like, no, God, if there is a God, there's no way that he would love someone like me.

35:33.378 --> 35:40.849
I'm selfish, I'm prideful, I mean, I say terrible things, I treat people wrong, and I just want, there's no way, I'm not lovable.

35:43.493 --> 35:49.522
But I'm sitting there that day in church, and I'm hearing this preacher talk about how God proved his love for us.

35:50.562 --> 35:54.206
by having Jesus die for those sins and rise again.

35:54.226 --> 35:55.588
Again, what is that?

35:55.888 --> 36:00.053
That is an idea or a series of ideas that come into our mind.

36:00.073 --> 36:04.458
And I heard those ideas that day and I felt God saying, I'm speaking to you.

36:04.498 --> 36:05.299
I'm speaking to you.

36:05.339 --> 36:05.839
It's true.

36:06.020 --> 36:06.620
I love you.

36:07.061 --> 36:07.541
It's true.

36:07.701 --> 36:08.462
I died for you.

36:10.485 --> 36:18.834
And it wasn't long after that that as a 17 year old kid, I decided to respond to those ideas and reach out and faith to God and receive Christ as my savior.

36:19.458 --> 36:20.579
And maybe that's you today.

36:21.900 --> 36:23.362
Maybe you need to hear these ideas.

36:23.742 --> 36:24.463
God loves you.

36:25.744 --> 36:33.211
No matter what you've done, no matter where you've been, how much you've sinned, or how much guilt you have, or maybe you were like me, you thought, man, there's no God that would life.

36:33.251 --> 36:33.771
There is a God.

36:33.972 --> 36:35.353
He would not love someone like me.

36:35.593 --> 36:36.454
Maybe that's where you're at.

36:36.474 --> 36:40.097
And I'm here to tell you today, you're exactly the person that he loves.

36:41.619 --> 36:49.266
And he sent Christ to die for you, to pay for those sins, to wash you and make you clean, just like he did me and many, many others.

36:50.562 --> 36:54.888
Maybe today you reach out to Him in faith and you say, Jesus, thank you for dying on the cross from my sin.

36:56.290 --> 36:57.893
Cleans me, wash me, make me your child.

36:58.534 --> 37:00.096
That is the ultimate upgrade.

37:01.017 --> 37:03.341
2 Corinthians chapter 5 verse 17 says it like this.

37:03.741 --> 37:07.186
Therefore, if anyone is in Christ, He's a new creation.

37:07.447 --> 37:11.032
The old is gone and the new has come.

37:11.352 --> 37:12.594
You talk about an upgrade.

37:14.530 --> 37:19.216
If you'd like to do that right now, if you'd like to upgrade your life and put your faith in Christ, I'm gonna say a simple prayer.

37:19.257 --> 37:20.819
Take these words and make them your own.

37:21.780 --> 37:23.963
Make this moment your moment of spiritual upgrade.

37:24.444 --> 37:25.105
Will you pray with me?

37:28.670 --> 37:36.781
Dear Jesus, I believe you died on the cross for me because you love me.

37:39.104 --> 37:40.626
I believe you paid for my sin.

37:44.514 --> 37:49.742
to remove the guilt, the shame, the penalty of sin.

37:51.665 --> 38:01.060
And right now, I ask you to cleanse me, wash me, and make me your child.

38:03.183 --> 38:09.613
I put my trust in you and what you did for me on the cross.

38:11.776 --> 38:12.978
Thank you for your grace.

38:14.690 --> 38:15.671
Thank you for your mercy.

38:17.214 --> 38:24.625
And from this day forward, teach me to love you, to honor you, and to obey you.

38:26.828 --> 38:27.990
It's in Jesus' name I pray.

38:29.251 --> 38:31.915
And everybody said, amen, amen.

38:31.995 --> 38:33.117
And can we give God glory?

38:33.878 --> 38:35.060
Come on, nice and loud, amen.

38:36.422 --> 38:39.186
If you trusted Christ, here's what I'd like you to do really quick.

38:39.778 --> 38:43.206
We'd like to grab your phone real quick and text the word save to 65248.

38:43.988 --> 38:50.043
We just want to get behind you and support you and let you know how you can thrive in your new walk with Christ.

38:50.063 --> 38:51.647
So text the word save to 65248.

38:52.128 --> 38:57.682
And after you do that, we would love to invite you to go back whatever location you're at.

38:57.730 --> 39:01.720
In the back of the auditorium and grab one of these boxes that says saved on it inside.

39:01.740 --> 39:03.344
There's a gift from us to you, a cup.

39:03.665 --> 39:08.296
There's a Bible with a reading plan for you to get you started on your new journey with Christ.

39:08.316 --> 39:09.740
So grab those on the way out.

39:09.780 --> 39:11.444
Can we give God glory one more time, guys?

39:11.524 --> 39:12.146
Amen.

